data.name: Diagram
desc: the base service for the diagram of the chart document.
The diagram is the object that contains the actual plot.
Different Diagram Types, e.g., PieDiagram or LineDiagram, can be instantiated by the com.sun.star.lang.XMultiServiceFactory of the XChartDocument.

properties.name: AutomaticPosition
desc: If this property is TRUE the position is calculated by the application automatically.

Setting this property to false will have no effect. Instead use the interface com.sun.star.drawing.XShape to set a concrete position (note com.sun.star.chart.XDiagram is derived from com.sun.star.drawing.XShape).

properties.name: AutomaticSize
desc: If this property is TRUE the size is calculated by the application automatically.

Setting this property to false will have no effect. Instead use the interface com.sun.star.drawing.XShape to set a concrete size (note com.sun.star.chart.XDiagram is derived from com.sun.star.drawing.XShape).

properties.name: DataCaption
desc: specifies how the caption of data points is displayed.

properties.name: DataRowSource
desc: determines if the data for a data row is contained in the columns or in the rows of the data array.

properties.name: MissingValueTreatment
desc: specifies how empty or invalid cells in the provided data should be handled when displayed
